134.jpg","cap":"Pioneer Historic Byway Hells Canyon Dam","desc":"This dam for Hells Canyon Reservoir regulates the water. Mountains form one side of the river and the white power plant stands beside the dam. Location: Hells Canyon Dam, Idaho (45.244° N 116.701° W) Status: Public domain. Photo taken by Tony Varilone","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Hells_Canyon_Dam_-_NARA_-_7721134.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fe/Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Hells_Canyon_Reservoir_-_NARA_-_7721135.jpg/1280px-Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Hells_Canyon_Reservoir_-_NARA_-_7721135.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fe/Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Hells_Canyon_Reservoir_-_NARA_-_7721135.jpg","cap":"Pioneer Historic Byway Hells Canyon Reservoir","desc":"Hells Canyon Reservoir flows peacefully around the base of the rocks. Wildflowers are blooming in the foreground. Location: Hells Canyon Reservoir, Idaho (45.237° N 116.703° W) Status: Public domain. Photo taken by Tony Varilone","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Hells_Canyon_Reservoir_-_NARA_-_7721135.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b9/Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Mirror_Images_-_NARA_-_7721136.jpg/1280px-Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Mirror_Images_-_NARA_-_7721136.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b9/Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Mirror_Images_-_NARA_-_7721136.jpg","cap":"Pioneer Historic Byway Mirror Images","desc":"The sky reflects this water at Hells Canyon Dam. Tall evergreen trees fill the riverbank. Location: Hells Canyon Dam, Idaho (45.241° N 116.702° W) Status: Public domain. Photo taken by Tony Varilone","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Pioneer_Historic_Byway_-_Mirror_Images_-_NARA_-_7721136.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons